	11 Feb 2005 David Gil <dgil@ossim.net> :
	* include/classes/Util.inc:
	  MySQL 4.1 returns TIMESTAMP as a string in 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS' format
	  MySQL 4.0 returns TIMESTAMP as a string in 'YYYYMMDDHHMMSS' format
	  New timestamp2date() solves this incompatibility problem.
	* scripts/test_diretive.pl: test new directive 12.

	10 Feb 2005 David Gil <dgil@ossim.net> :
	* Drawing RRDs: Don't expand the lower and upper limit if the graph
	  contains a value outside the valid range (threshold*2,5).
	* www/top.php: menu enhancements.

